verbose_text: It is now understood that accumulation of DAMPs, such as by-products of necrotic cells, extracellular ATP, ceramides, saturated fatty acids, uric acid, amyloid fibrils, or free cholesterol crystals, are sensed by pattern recognition receptors (PRRs) in macrophages to trigger chronic low-grade inflammation seen during aging.
